Hi Dave,



We have been playing with the opposed diffusion flame code (Very
impressive!) and wish to apply it to some methane flame-doping experiments
that we are doing.  For this, we need to add several new species for which
thermo and transport data is fleeting.  I am using  group additivity  data
to estimate thermo properties.  I am now at the point of trying to add NASA
coefficients into the "cti" file we are creating.  The problem is that I am
a bit confused about the form for the enthalpy that goes into the file.  The
documentation (cti.pdf, Eqn. 4.2) suggests a slightly different form than
the old Chemkin-II approach.  (In particular, should the sixth coefficient
be divided by temperature.) I have started to reverse engineer by running
through the same process with a known molecule, but I thought it might be
both more efficient to ask you, and clarify this for others as well.
